== Modes

A flash toy can be run in one of the following modes:
* MODE_DEMO: illustrates the toy features
* MODE_EDIT: allows users to edit settings
* MODE_TOY:  runs in real site with the edited settings

== Typical structure of a toy

package {
	public class Document extends Sprite {
		public static const MODE_DEMO:int = 0;
		public static const MODE_EDIT:int = 1;
		public static const MODE_TOY:int  = 2;

		private var _mode:int;

		public function Document():void {
			// Determine the running mode
			var flashVars:Object = this.root.loaderInfo.parameters;
			if (flashVars != null) {
				if (flashVars["mode"] == "demo") {
					_mode = MODE_DEMO;
				} else if (flashVars["mode"] == "edit") {
					_mode = MODE_EDIT;
				} else {
					_mode = MODE_TOY;
				}
			} else {
				_mode = MODE_TOY;
			}

			// ...
		}
	}
}
